    <h2>SECTION A: Attempt any TWO question.</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>What is a system of linear equations ? When the system is consistent ? Find the condition on g, h, k that makes the system consistent.</p>
<p>x<sub>1</sub> – 4x<sub>2</sub> + 7x<sub>3</sub> = g</p>
<p>3x<sub>2</sub> – 5x<sub>3</sub> = h</p>
<p>-2x<sub>1</sub> + 5x<sub>2</sub> – 9x<sub>3</sub> = k</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>A system of linear equations is a collection of one or more linear equations involving one or more variables. Each equation in the system is a linear combination of the variables, and the goal is to find values for the variables that satisfy all the equations simultaneously. In general, a system of linear equations can be represented as follows:</p>
<p>a₁x₁ + a₂x₂ + a₃x₃ + … + aₙxₙ = b₁<br />
a₁’x₁ + a₂’x₂ + a₃’x₃ + … + aₙ’xₙ = b₂<br />
a₁”x₁ + a₂”x₂ + a₃”x₃ + … + aₙ”xₙ = b₃<br />
…<br />
a₁ᵤx₁ + a₂ᵤx₂ + a₃ᵤx₃ + … + aₙᵤxₙ = bᵤ</p>
<p>Where:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>x₁, x₂, x₃, …, xₙ are the variables.</li>
<li>a₁, a₂, a₃, …, aₙ are the coefficients of the variables in the first equation.</li>
<li>b₁ is the constant on the right side of the first equation.</li>
<li>Similarly, a₁’, a₂’, a₃’, …, aₙ’, b₂, a₁”, a₂”, a₃”, …, aₙ”, b₃, and so on represent the coefficients and constants in the subsequent equations.</li>
</ul>
<p>A system of linear equations is consistent when it has at least one solution, which means there is a set of values for the variables that satisfies all the equations in the system. In other words, a system of equations is consistent if there is at least one combination of values for the variables that makes all the equations true simultaneously.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 2</h3>
<div><p><p>$$ Let A =\begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 & -5 & -7 \\<br />
-3 & 7 & 5 \\<br />
\end{bmatrix} , u = \begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 \\<br />
2\\<br />
3\\<br />
\end{bmatrix}, b= \begin{bmatrix}<br />
-2\\<br />
-2\\<br />
\end{bmatrix},$$</p>
<p>and define a transformation T : R<sup>3</sup> → R² by T(x) = Ax then</p>
<p>a. find T(u).</p>
<p>b. Find x ∈ R<sup>3</sup> whose image under T is b.</p>
<p>c. Is x unique ?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>given,</p>
<p>$$  A =\begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 &amp; -5 &amp; -7 \\<br />
-3 &amp; 7 &amp; 5 \\<br />
\end{bmatrix} ,<br />
u = \begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 \\<br />
2\\<br />
3\\<br />
\end{bmatrix},<br />
b= \begin{bmatrix}<br />
-2\\<br />
-2\\<br />
\end{bmatrix},$$</p>
<p>T : R<sup>3</sup> → R² by T(x) = Ax then</p>
<p>a.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">T(u) = Au</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">$$=\begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 &amp; -5 &amp; -7 \\<br />
-3 &amp; 7 &amp; 5 \\<br />
\end{bmatrix}<br />
\begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 \\<br />
2\\<br />
3\\<br />
\end{bmatrix}$$</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">$$=\begin{bmatrix}<br />
-27\\<br />
26\\<br />
\end{bmatrix}$$</p>
<p>b.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">T(x) = b</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">$$let x = \begin{bmatrix}<br />
x_{{1}}\\<br />
x_{{2}}\\<br />
x_{{3}}\\<br />
\end{bmatrix}$$ then,</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">or,  Ax = b</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"> $$or, \begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 &amp; -5 &amp; -7 \\<br />
-3 &amp; 7 &amp; 5 \\<br />
\end{bmatrix}<br />
\begin{bmatrix}<br />
1 \\<br />
2\\<br />
3\\<br />
\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}<br />
x_{{1}}\\<br />
x_{{2}}\\<br />
x_{{3}}\\<br />
\end{bmatrix}$$</p>
<p>Multiply Equation 1 by 3 to eliminate <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">x<sub>1</sub></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> when we add the two equations:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="base"><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">15</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">21</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3 </span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">6</span></span><br />
<span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mbin">+ </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">7</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mbin">+ </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">5</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">2</span></span></p>
<p>Adding these equations:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">8</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">16</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">8</span></span></p>
<p>Simplifying, we find:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mbin">+ </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">2</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">1</span></span></p>
<p>Now, using <span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2 </span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">1 </span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">2</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, substitute into Equation 1 to solve for <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">x<sub>1</sub></span><sub><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></sub></span>:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1 </span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">5</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mbin">−</span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">2</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mclose">) </span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">7</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">2</span></span><br />
<span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1 </span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">5 </span><span class="mbin">+ </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">10</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mbin">− </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">7</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mord">2</span></span><br />
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"> <span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></span><span class="mbin">+ </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><sub><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​ </span></span></span></span></sub></span><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord">3</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p>Thus, we can express the solution as:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-43092" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/WhatsApp-Image-2024-10-18-at-3.03.05-PM.jpeg" alt="" width="131" height="80"></p>
<p>where <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">x</span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><sub><span class="vlist"><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></sub><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is a free variable. This represents the set of all <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">x</span></span> in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">R<sup>3</sup></span></span> that satisfy <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml">T(x) </span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="mrel">= </span></span><span class="base"><span class="mord mathnormal">b</span></span></span></span>.</p>
